 {"id":"bd-17cn","title":"Idea: Hook decision cache for repeated commands","description":"## Background
Many agents run the same build/test commands repeatedly. Caching classification + gating decisions can shave microseconds and reduce CPU overhead.

## Goals
- Cache recent command decisions (classification + gating outcome).
- Keep cache small and time-bounded to avoid stale decisions.

## Design / Approach
- Add LRU cache keyed by command string + working directory + env overrides.
- TTL-based expiration (e.g., 30s).
- Ensure structural checks (pipes/background) are still honored.

## Tasks / Subtasks
- Implement small LRU cache in hook.
- Add metrics to track cache hit rate.
- Provide config for max entries and TTL.

## Tests
- Unit: cache hits/misses and TTL expiry.
- Integration: repeated command uses cache without changing outcome.

## Acceptance Criteria
- Cache improves repeated decision latency without behavior changes.

## Logging & E2E
- E2E script: scripts/e2e_bd-17cn.sh (one script per bead unless intentionally combined).
- Logging format: JSONL via TestLogger (tests/true_e2e/logging.rs) or scripts/test_lib.sh log_json.
- Required fields: ts, test, phase, worker, command, bytes_transferred, duration_ms, result, error (if any).
- Phases to log (as applicable): classify, select, sync_up, exec, sync_down, cleanup, summary.
- Include a final summary block with pass/fail counts and total elapsed time.

## Edge Cases & UX
- Cache key includes config hash + env allowlist to avoid staleness.
- TTL expiry enforced; max size bounded.
- No caching for commands that are structurally rejected.

## E2E Outline
- Repeated command uses cache (timing log shows hit).
- Config change invalidates cache.

## Unit Tests (Detailed)
- rch/src/hook.rs: LRU cache hit/miss + TTL expiry.
- config change invalidates cache.

## E2E Script Notes
- scripts/e2e_bd-17cn.sh: repeated command shows cache hit in logs.
