 {"id":"bd-17hq","title":"Add --verbose flag consistently to all CLI commands","description":"# Add --verbose Flag to All Commands

## Problem
The --verbose flag is defined globally in main.rs (line 107) but not all commands use it. Users expect `rch workers list --verbose` to show more details.

## Commands Missing --verbose Behavior

### rch workers list
Current: Shows basic worker info
With --verbose: Should additionally show:
- Last probe timestamp
- Circuit breaker state
- Speed score history
- Recent job count
- SSH connection status

### rch self-test
Current: Shows pass/fail only
With --verbose: Should show:
- Each test step as it runs
- Timing for each phase
- Worker selection reasoning
- Transfer size and speed
- Compilation output

### rch queue
Current: Shows active builds
With --verbose: Should show:
- Queue position and ETA
- Resource requirements
- Why each build is waiting
- Worker assignment reasoning

### rch status
Current: Summary only
With --verbose: Should show:
- All worker details
- Active job details
- Recent build stats
- Config source info

## Implementation Pattern
In each command handler, check `cli.verbose`:

```rust
pub async fn workers_list(verbose: bool, json: bool) -> Result<()> {
    let workers = get_workers().await?;

    if json {
        // JSON always includes all fields
        output_json(&workers)?;
    } else if verbose {
        // Verbose: extra columns, more rows
        print_workers_verbose(&workers)?;
    } else {
        // Normal: compact summary
        print_workers_compact(&workers)?;
    }
}
```

