## Purpose

Establish the foundational infrastructure needed to run true end-to-end tests against real workers. This includes test harness utilities, worker discovery, output comparison helpers, and CI/local run configuration.

## Why This Comes First

All other true e2e tests depend on this infrastructure. Without a proper harness that can:
1. Discover available workers
2. Skip gracefully when no workers available
3. Compare local vs remote output
4. Clean up test artifacts

...the individual tests would each need to reinvent this logic, leading to duplication and inconsistency.

## MANDATORY Logging Standards

All tests and utilities in this infrastructure MUST implement structured JSON logging:

### Log Format Specification

```json
{
  "ts": "2026-01-19T12:00:00.123Z",
  "level": "INFO|WARN|ERROR|DEBUG",
  "test": "test_cargo_build",
  "phase": "setup|sync|execute|validate|teardown",
  "worker": "css|local|null",
  "duration_ms": 1234,
  "msg": "Human-readable message",
  "data": { /* phase-specific structured data */ }
}
```

### Required Log Events

1. **Test Start**: test name, worker target, fixture paths
2. **Phase Transitions**: setup→sync→execute→validate→teardown with timing
3. **Command Execution**: full command, args, working directory
4. **Output Capture**: stdout/stderr size, truncation if any
5. **Comparison Results**: match/mismatch, diff summary if failed
6. **Test End**: pass/fail/skip, total duration, cleanup status

### Logger Interface

```rust
pub struct TestLogger {
    test_name: String,
    log_file: BufWriter<File>,
    start_time: Instant,
    current_phase: Option<String>,
}

impl TestLogger {
    pub fn new(test_name: &str) -> std::io::Result<Self>;
    pub fn phase(&mut self, name: &str);
    pub fn info(&mut self, msg: &str, data: serde_json::Value);
    pub fn warn(&mut self, msg: &str, data: serde_json::Value);
    pub fn error(&mut self, msg: &str, data: serde_json::Value);
    pub fn finish(self) -> TestResult;
}
```

### Log File Location

- Per-test logs: `target/true_e2e_logs/{test_name}_{timestamp}.jsonl`
- Combined log: `target/true_e2e_logs/combined_{run_id}.jsonl`
- Human-readable summary: `target/true_e2e_logs/summary_{run_id}.txt`

## Technical Requirements

### Test Harness (`tests/true_e2e/harness.rs`)

```rust
pub struct TrueE2EHarness {
    daemon_socket: PathBuf,
    available_workers: Vec<WorkerInfo>,
    test_project_root: PathBuf,
    logger: TestLogger,  // MANDATORY: every harness has a logger
}

impl TrueE2EHarness {
    /// Create harness with logger, skip test if no real workers available
    pub fn new_or_skip(test_name: &str) -> Result<Self, SkipReason>;

    /// Run command locally and capture output (logs execution details)
    pub fn run_local(&mut self, cmd: &str) -> CommandOutput;

    /// Run command via RCH hook and capture output (logs execution details)
    pub fn run_via_rch(&mut self, cmd: &str) -> CommandOutput;

    /// Compare outputs, logs diff details on mismatch
    pub fn assert_outputs_match(&mut self, local: &CommandOutput, remote: &CommandOutput);
}
```

### Output Comparison Strategy

Not all output will be byte-identical. We need configurable comparison that ignores:
- Absolute paths (replace with relative or placeholder)
- Timestamps in compilation output
- Worker hostnames in debug output
- Order of parallel compilation units

Comparison must log:
- What normalization was applied
- Original vs normalized content hashes
- Line-by-line diff for mismatches

### Skip Logic

Tests must skip gracefully when:
- No daemon running
- No workers configured
- All workers unreachable
- Required toolchain not on workers

Use `#[ignore]` attribute plus custom skip macro that logs why (with structured JSON).

### CI Configuration

Add Cargo feature `true-e2e` that:
- Gates the `tests/true_e2e/` module
- Defaults to OFF in CI (no workers there)
- Documents how to run locally with workers
- Sets log output directory via env var

