-{"id":"bd-3tqu","title":"EPIC: Eliminate all stub/placeholder code - make RCH 100% real and functional","description":"# Epic: Stub Elimination - 100% Real Functionality

## Background
During real e2e testing on 2026-01-30, it was discovered that multiple critical features in RCH are implemented as stubs that pretend to work but do nothing. This creates a false sense of functionality and prevents the system from actually working.

## Problem Statement
The codebase contains numerous functions that:
1. Accept parameters but ignore them
2. Sleep to simulate work
3. Always return success
4. Log fake progress
5. Never perform actual operations

This is UNACCEPTABLE for production software.

## Philosophy
"Code review found no bugs" means nothing if the code was never actually run.
Static analysis cannot find stub implementations.
Only real e2e testing reveals these issues.

## Scope
All stub/placeholder code must be replaced with real implementations.

## Discovered Stubs

### Critical (P0)
| Stub | Location | Impact |
|------|----------|--------|
| fleet deploy | fleet/executor.rs:288-310 | Workers never get updated binaries |
| self-test | daemon API handler | Cannot verify system works |

### High (P1)  
| Stub | Location | Impact |
|------|----------|--------|
| hook_test | commands/mod.rs:8599 | Cannot verify hook classification |
| agents_install_hook | commands/mod.rs:8809 | Cannot install hooks for other agents |
| agents_uninstall_hook | commands/mod.rs:8815 | Cannot remove hooks |
| checksum verification | update/mod.rs:162 | Security vulnerability |

### Medium (P2)
| Stub | Location | Impact |
|------|----------|--------|
| benchmark_scheduler | benchmark_scheduler.rs:583 | SpeedScores are never real |
| rsync --stats | transfer.rs:442 | Wrong transfer reporting |
| fleet rollback | fleet/rollback.rs | Cannot recover from bad deploys |

### Low (P3)
| Stub | Location | Impact |
|------|----------|--------|
| changelog_diff | update/check.rs:142 | Users don't see what changed |

## Success Criteria
1. Every command that reports success must actually do work
2. Every "progress" indicator must reflect real progress
3. Every test that passes must test real functionality
4. `rch doctor` must catch configuration issues
5. E2e test suite must verify complete workflow

## Child Beads
- bd-273k: fleet deploy stub
- bd-130u: rsync --stats
- bd-4g4a: hook_test stub
- bd-3uo5: agent hook stubs
- bd-34jb: benchmark_scheduler stub
- bd-16v3: checksum verification
- bd-177o: changelog_diff
- bd-25ve: self-test hanging
- bd-2gop: fleet rollback

## Testing Strategy
After all stubs are fixed:
1. Fresh install on new machine
2. Configure workers from scratch
3. Run `rch doctor` - all checks pass
4. Run `rch fleet deploy` - binaries actually transferred
5. Run `rch self-test` - remote compilation works
6. Run `rch hook test --full` - e2e pipeline verified

## Definition of Done
- All commands perform their advertised function
- No code contains "// TODO", "// STUB", "// placeholder"
- Integration tests cover all command paths
- Manual e2e test passes on fresh system
